# Product Requirements Document (PRD)  
## Product: ReconnectAI  


---

## 1. Overview

ReconnectAI is a CRM-agnostic AI layer that activates dormant client databases for real estate agents by delivering personalized, high-value market insights at scale, driving referrals and repeat business.

---

## 2. Goals & Objectives

### Primary Goal
Increase revenue generated from past clients.

### Secondary Goals
- Improve client engagement rates  
- Increase referral frequency  
- Reduce manual outreach effort  

---

## 3. Success Metrics

### North Star
- Revenue from past clients (per agent)

### Key Metrics
- CRM activation rate (% usable contacts)  
- Message engagement rate (open/reply)  
- Re-engagement rate (inactive → active)  
- Referral rate per 100 clients  
- Listings generated from past clients  

---

## 4. Target Users

### Primary
- Individual real estate agents (200–1,000 contacts)

### Secondary
- Real estate teams  
- Brokerages  

---

## 5. User Problems

- “I don’t have time to follow up with all my past clients.”  
- “My CRM is outdated and messy.”  
- “I don’t know what to say to clients unless they want to sell.”  
- “I lose deals to agents who stay top-of-mind.”  

---

## 6. Product Scope (MVP)

### 6.1 CRM Integration Layer
- CSV upload  
- Google Sheets sync  
- API integration (basic)  

---

### 6.2 Data Processing
- Deduplication  
- Field mapping  
- Basic enrichment  
- Tagging (owner, investor, etc.)

---

### 6.3 Intelligence Engine
- Detect:
  - Nearby property sales  
  - Price changes  
  - Market trends  

---

### 6.4 Personalization Engine
- Match insights → relevant clients  
- Template-based personalization  

---

### 6.5 Messaging System
- Channels:
  - Email  
  - WhatsApp (via API)  

- Modes:
  - Auto-send  
  - Approval required  
  - Draft-only  

---

### 6.6 Dashboard (Basic)
- Contact activation status  
- Messages sent  
- Engagement metrics  

---

## 7. Out of Scope (MVP)

- Full CRM replacement  
- Advanced predictive analytics  
- Fully autonomous AI conversations  
- Multi-industry expansion  

---

## 8. User Flows

### Flow 1: Onboarding
1. Upload CRM / connect integration  
2. System cleans and structures data  
3. User reviews segmentation  
4. User sets preferences (tone, frequency)  

---

### Flow 2: Message Trigger
1. Market event detected  
2. System matches relevant clients  
3. Message generated  
4. Sent automatically or queued for approval  

---

### Flow 3: Engagement
1. Client receives message  
2. Client replies or clicks  
3. Agent notified  
4. Agent follows up manually  

---

## 9. Functional Requirements

### CRM Layer
- Support CSV import  
- Support API ingestion  
- Handle inconsistent schemas  

---

### Intelligence Engine
- Ingest property transaction data  
- Detect triggers (rules-based MVP)  

---

### Personalization
- Insert dynamic variables (name, property, location)  
- Generate natural language messages  

---

### Messaging
- Queue system  
- Scheduling  
- Channel routing  

---

### Dashboard
- View contact segments  
- View sent messages  
- View engagement metrics  

---

## 10. Non-Functional Requirements

- Scalable to 10,000+ contacts per agent  
- Message latency < 5 minutes after trigger  
- Data privacy compliance (PDPA/GDPR where applicable)  
- High reliability for message delivery  

---

## 11. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|--------|
| Poor CRM data | Strong onboarding + cleaning |
| Low engagement | High relevance filtering |
| Integration complexity | Multiple ingestion methods |
| Trust in AI | Approval workflows |

---

## 12. Dependencies

- Property market data sources  
- Messaging APIs (WhatsApp, email)  
- CRM APIs / integration tools  

---

